  "text": "The video clips are segmented into shots using the algorithm by Naphade et al. [CITATION_1] . We then use the spatio-temporal segmentation in [CITATION_2] applied separately to each shot to obtain regions ho- mogeneous in color and motion. Depending on the genre of the movie and the story line, shots may range from a few frames to a few hundred frames. For large shots, artificial cuts are introduced every 2 s. This ensures, that the spatio-temporal tracking and segmentation does not break down due to appearance and disappearance of regions. The segmentation and tracking algorithm uses color, edge, and motion to perform segmentation and computes the optical flow for motion estimation. Fig. 9 shows a video frame and its segmented version with six dominant segments. These segments are labeled manually to create the ground truth. Since they are tracked within each shot using optical flow, the labels can be propagated to instances of the segments in all the frames within the shot.",
